explanations.reason: The paper focuses on the role of ancillary service markets (ASMs) in promoting intermittent renewable energy integration during the COVID-19 demand shock in China. It does not mention or utilize any machine learning techniques, algorithms, or models, nor does it discuss any related concepts such as supervised learning, unsupervised learning, reinforcement learning, neural networks, or any other AI-related methodologies. The study is primarily an economic and policy analysis rather than a technical or computational one.
